        <h1>LeetCode 1758: Minimum Changes To Make Alternating Binary String (C++)</h1>
        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                You are given a string s consisting only of characters '0' and '1'. In one operation, you can change any
                '0' to '1' or vice versa. The string is called alternating if no two adjacent characters are equal.
                Return the minimum number of operations needed to make s alternating.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: s = "0100"<br>
                Output: 1<br>
                Explanation: Change the second character to '1', resulting in "0110". This is not alternating, but
                changing index 2 gives "0101" which is alternating. Minimum operations = 1.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    int minOperations(string t) {
        int n = t.size();
        int a = 0, b = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i &lt; n; i++) {
            // Check both alternating patterns together
            if (i &amp; 1) {
                a += t[i] != '1';
                b += t[i] != '0';
            } else {
                a += t[i] != '0';
                b += t[i] != '1';
            }
        }
        return min(a, b);
    }
};</code></pre>
